    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Multidraw Context</para>
<para>This class incapsulates logic of filling multidraw buffers. It implements draw call id/per draw parameters passing for different platforms and manages buffers required for it. <parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>PerDrawDataT</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Type of per draw parameters structure. If only draw call id is required, use uint32_t. When dword is enough there won&apos;t be any indirection for per draw parameter reading in the shader. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>DrawIdBits</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Number of bits used for draw call id storage inside draw arguments structure. Default is 20 bits. Other bits could be used by user for per draw data, so this data could be read without indirections. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
